@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{zotra-extras.el} extends @samp{zotra}, the Emacs package that fetches bibliographic metadata using Zotero translation servers. While @samp{zotra} provides the core fetching mechanism, @samp{zotra-extras.el} wraps it in a richer workflow that integrates with @samp{ebib} for entry management, supports VPN routing for geo-restricted sources, and handles common error conditions gracefully.

The package provides the following capabilities:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Enhanced entry addition.} An improved version of @code{zotra-add-entry} that auto-detects URLs from Elfeed and EWW buffers, falls back to an alternative backend on server errors, and automatically opens the new entry in @samp{ebib} for review and processing (@ref{Adding entries}).
@item
@strong{Batch processing.} A command to add multiple bibliographic entries from a file containing one URL per line (@ref{Batch processing}).
@item
@strong{VPN integration.} Optional routing of IMDb requests through Mullvad VPN to control the geographic origin of fetched metadata (@ref{VPN for IMDb}).
@item
@strong{Org protocol handler.} A protocol handler that enables adding entries directly from a web browser (@ref{Org protocol handler}).
@item
@strong{Bib@TeX{} cleanup.} Post-processing functions that fix octal encoding artifacts, set timestamps, and clean up newly imported entries (@ref{Bib@TeX{} cleanup}).
@item
@strong{Field fetching.} A utility function to retrieve a single bibliographic field for a URL without adding the full entry, with support for skipping excluded domains (@ref{Fetching fields}).
@end itemize

The package depends on @samp{zotra} and @samp{paths}, and optionally integrates with @samp{ebib}, @samp{ebib-extras}, @samp{mullvad}, @samp{org-ref}, and @samp{tlon}.

