@node Adding entries
@section Adding entries

@findex zotra-extras-add-entry
The command @code{zotra-extras-add-entry} is the primary entry point for importing bibliographic metadata. It improves on the standard @code{zotra-add-entry} in several ways:

@itemize
@item
@strong{URL auto-detection.} When invoked from an @samp{elfeed-show-mode} buffer, it copies the current entry's URL to the kill ring. In @samp{eww-mode}, it copies the current page URL@. In other modes, it pre-fills the prompt with the most recent kill ring entry.
@item
@strong{Bibliography file selection.} If no BIBFILE argument is provided, it prompts the user to choose one via @code{zotra-extras-set-bibfile} (@ref{Bibliography file selection}) and stores the choice in the variable @code{zotra-extras-most-recent-bibfile}.
@item
@strong{VPN routing.} When @code{zotra-extras-use-mullvad-p} is non-nil and the URL matches @samp{imdb.com}, the command connects through Mullvad VPN before fetching (@ref{VPN for IMDb}).
@item
@strong{ISBN fallback via Google Books.} When the input is a bare ISBN (10 or 13 digits) and the translation server's search translators return no results, the command automatically retries by looking up the ISBN on Google Books (@ref{ISBN fallback}).
@item
@strong{Backend fallback.} If the primary @samp{zotra} backend fails with a JSON parse error indicating an internal server error, the command automatically retries with the @samp{citoid} backend.
@item
@strong{Ebib integration.} After successfully adding the entry, it opens the new entry in @samp{ebib} for review, unless the optional DO-NOT-OPEN argument is non-nil.
@end itemize

The optional arguments URL-OR-SEARCH-STRING, ENTRY-FORMAT, BIBFILE, and DO-NOT-OPEN can be supplied programmatically for non-interactive use.

@node Bibliography file selection
@section Bibliography file selection

@findex zotra-extras-set-bibfile
The command @code{zotra-extras-set-bibfile} prompts the user to choose a bibliography file from a predefined list of candidates: @code{tlon-file-fluid}, @code{tlon-file-db}, and @code{paths-file-personal-bibliography-new}. The selected file path is returned. This command is called by @code{zotra-extras-add-entry} when no bibliography file is specified (@ref{Adding entries}).

@node Batch processing
@section Batch processing

@findex zotra-extras-add-multiple-urls-from-file
When you need to import many entries at once, the command @code{zotra-extras-add-multiple-urls-from-file} reads a file containing one URL per line and adds a bibliographic entry for each URL to a chosen bibliography file. Interactively, it prompts for both the file path (defaulting to the downloads directory) and the target bibliography via @code{zotra-extras-set-bibfile}. Duplicate URLs in the file are removed before processing.

Each entry is added without opening it in @samp{ebib} individually, avoiding repeated window switching. After all entries have been processed, the command opens the bibliography in @samp{ebib} and sorts by timestamp so the newly added entries appear together.

The constant @code{zotra-extras-add-multiple-urls-from-file} (the variable, not the command) holds the default file path for the URL list, set to @samp{zotra-add-multiple-urls.txt} in the downloads directory.

